'''Ren-Quarr''' was a [[Quarren/Legends|Quarren]]<ref name="CSWE" /> barfly<ref name="Who's Who">{{InsiderCite|75|Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night}}</ref> with [[Color/Legends|orange]] skin<ref name="Episode 2" /> and well-groomed [[Limb/Legends|tentacles]]. He frequented the [[Outlander Club/Legends|Outlander Club]],<ref name="CSWE" /> a [[Nightclub/Legends|nightclub]] and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]] hall located in the [[Uscru Entertainment District/Legends|Uscru Entertainment District]] of the<ref name="Club">{{CSWECite|II|431|Outlander Club}}</ref> [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="aotcvis">''[[Star Wars: Attack of the Clones: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]],<ref name="Club" /> prior to the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|outbreak]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]<ref name="CSWE" /> in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|II}} to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].</ref>

During a [[Standard day/Legends|night]]<ref name="Episode 2" /> in that [[Standard year/Legends|year]],<ref name="NEC" /> he was present in the Outlander Club as [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] entered, [[Plot to assassinate Senator Amidala/Legends|searching]] for [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Zam Wesell/Legends|Zam Wesell]].<ref name="Episode 2" /> As Skywalker walked around the club, he<ref name="Episode 2" /> lurked<ref name="Who's Who" /> behind<ref name="Episode 2" /> the [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] [[Lunae Minx/Legends|Lunae Minx]] and the criminal [[Achk Med-Beq/Legends|Achk Med-Beq]].<ref name="Who's Who" /> Being a Quarren, Ren-Quarr's [[Species/Legends|species]] added to the interplanetary feel of the club on that night.<ref name="FF">{{FactFile|96|OUT 1-2|Outlander Nightclub Patrons}}</ref> He wore dark colored [[Clothing/Legends|clothing]] while at the club.<ref name="Episode 2" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Given that Squid Heads are known as Quarren, this barfly's name is more akin to a nonalien character introducing himself as “Mann Hugh"|Daniel Wallace|<ref name="Who's Who" />}}
Ren-Quarr first appeared in the [[2002]] [[prequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="Episode 2" /> The Outlander Club scenes including Ren-Quarr were shot at [[Fox Studios, Sydney]] on [[July 17]], [[2000]].<ref name="Mythmaking">''[[Mythmaking: Behind the Scenes of Attack of the Clones]]''</ref> Prior to the film's release, the character was first pictured in the documentary "[[Making Episode II Webdocs|A Twinkle Beyond Pluto]],"<ref name="ATBP">{{SW|url=video/a-twinkle-beyond-pluto|series=Making Episode II Webdocs|text=Part 5: A Twinkle Beyond Pluto}}</ref> released on [[July 31]], [[2001]].<ref name="ATBP Date">{{SWArchive|url=episode-ii/bts/me2/archive.html|text=''Making Episode II Webdocs'' archive}}</ref>

The character's name first appeared in the [[StarWars.com]] web article "[[Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases]]," published on [[May 2]], [[2003]], where it was applied to a picture of<ref name="Cantina Roll-Call">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iv/bts/article/f20030502/index.html|text=Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases|int=Cantina Roll-Call: Shedding Light on Some Alien Aliases}}</ref> the Quarren [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Tikkes/Legends|Tikkes]].<ref name="CSWE2">{{CSWECite|III|248|Tikkes}}</ref> The name would first be applied to the character seen in Episode II in the article "[[Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night]]," published in the [[Star Wars Insider 75|seventy-fifth]] issue of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine<ref name="Who's Who" /> on [[April 6]], [[2004]].<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=community/fanclub/mag/news20040315.html|text=The New Face of Evil}}</ref> The author of the article, [[Daniel Wallace]], commented that Ren-Quarr's name is akin to a nonalien character introducing himself as Mann Hugh and that his groomed tentacles gave him the appearance of a [[Wikipedia:Rollie Fingers|Rollie Fingers]]-style [[Wikipedia:Handlebar moustache|handlebar mustache]].<ref name="Who's Who" />

